# Drizzle — both `.sql` migration files AND the `meta/` journal/snapshot
# directories MUST be tracked. Drizzle-kit reads _journal.json to determine
# which migrations have been applied and 0000_snapshot.json (etc.) to diff
# the current schema against. Fresh-clone installs will fail with ENOENT
# without these. The `.sql` is the source of truth for DDL; the journal +
# snapshot are bookkeeping that must stay in sync.
# packages/db/src/migrations/   (tracked)
# packages/db/src/migrations/meta  (tracked)

# pnpm
.pnpm-debug.log*

# Local scratch — ad-hoc probes, dump files; not part of the build, not
# committed, not linted. Add via `.scratch/...` from the repo root.
